# Lynoria UI Library v4.0 🎨 - The Ultimate Guide

Welcome to the complete, exhaustive guide for **Lynoria UI Library v4.0**. This document is designed for developers and script makers who want to understand every single capability of this library.

Lynoria is a premium, high-performance UI library designed for Roblox exploit scripts. It features a macOS-inspired aesthetic, automatic configuration saving/loading, and a dynamic color palette system.

---

## 🚀 1. Bootstrapping (Initialization)

To use Lynoria in your script, you load it via a raw GitHub URL using `loadstring`.

```lua
-- Load the library
local Lynoria = loadstring(game:HttpGet(""))()

-- Create the main window (Pass the title of your script)
local Win = Lynoria.new("My Script Name")

-- Set the bottom-left status indicator (true = Green/Updated, false = Red/Down)
Win:SetStatus(true) 
```

**What happens here?**
* The library creates the UI in `CoreGui` (or `PlayerGui` as fallback).
* It automatically creates a `Lynoria` folder in your workspace directory (for configs and themes).
* It auto-loads the last used theme and configuration if they exist.

