## 💾 4. The `Flags` System (State Management)

If you don't want to use callback functions for everything, you can read the current state of any component at any time using `Win.Flags`. 

This is highly recommended for loops (like Aimbot or ESP loops).

```lua
-- Inside a RunService loop:
if Win.Flags["Aimbot"] and Win.Flags["Aimbot"].Value == true then
    local currentFov = Win.Flags["FOV"].Value
    local currentHitbox = Win.Flags["Hitbox"].Value
    -- Do aimbot math here...
end
```

