## 🎨 7. For Advanced Devs: Adding Default Themes

If you are modifying the source code of `Lynoria.lua` and want to add new default themes for everyone, look at the `Presets` table at the very top of the script (line ~15).

A valid theme requires these exact color keys:
```lua
local Presets = {
    MyCustomTheme = {
        Bg = Color3.fromRGB(0, 0, 0),
        Bg2 = Color3.fromRGB(8, 8, 8),
        Surface = Color3.fromRGB(16, 16, 16),
        SurfHover = Color3.fromRGB(24, 24, 24),
        SurfActive = Color3.fromRGB(32, 32, 32),
        Border = Color3.fromRGB(30, 30, 30),
        Text = Color3.fromRGB(255, 255, 255),
        TextDim = Color3.fromRGB(170, 170, 170),
        TextMuted = Color3.fromRGB(90, 90, 90),
        Green = Color3.fromRGB(50, 215, 75),  -- Only used for the Status Dot
        Red = Color3.fromRGB(255, 69, 58),    -- Only used for UI close button
        Yellow = Color3.fromRGB(255, 214, 10),-- Only used for UI minimize button
        ToggleOn = Color3.fromRGB(255, 69, 58), -- MAIN ACCENT COLOR (Sliders, Toggles, Active Tabs)
        ToggleOff = Color3.fromRGB(38, 38, 40),
        SliderFill = Color3.fromRGB(255, 69, 58), -- Matches ToggleOn
        SliderTrack = Color3.fromRGB(38, 38, 40)
    }
}
```
*Note: In v4.0, the "Accent" color is primarily driven by `ToggleOn` and `SliderFill`.*

